  "prompt": "What are some good libraries in Mumbai?",
  "response": "Mumbai, one of India\u2019s largest and most vibrant cities, is home to several excellent libraries that cater to a wide range of interests. Here are a few notable ones:\n\n1. **Asiatic Society Library (Town Hall Library)**:\n   - Location: Fort\n   - Highlights: Established in 1804, this historic library contains over 100,000 books, ancient manuscripts, rare collection, periodicals, and it is housed in a beautiful neo-classical building. \n\n2. **David Sassoon Library**:\n   - Location: Kala Ghoda\n   - Highlights: Founded in 1847, featuring periodical sections, reading rooms, and a serene garden area. It is popular among researchers and those seeking a quiet reading space.\n\n3. **Dr. Bhau Daji Lad Museum Library**:\n   - Location: Byculla\n   - Highlights: Established in 1872, it offers a wide array of archives and reference material related to Mumbai\u2019s history and cultural heritage.\n\n4. **British Council Library**:\n   - Location: Nariman Point\n   - Highlights: Known for its extensive collection of contemporary English books, periodicals, DVDs, and digital resources. Membership provides access to global resources and online services.\n\n5. **J N Petit Institute Library**:\n   - Location: Fort\n   - Highlights: It is over a century old and boasts a substantial collection of books across various genres including fiction, non-fiction, research materials, and rare books.\n\n6. **KITAB KHANA**:\n   - Location: Fort\n   - Highlights: Though primarily a bookstore, Kitab Khana includes a reading space with a curated collection of books. It\u2019s known for its cozy ambiance and literary events.\n\n7. **Narsee Monjee Institute Library**:\n   - Location: Vile Parle\n   - Highlights: Part of the NMIMS university, this library caters primarily to students but offers a wide range of academic resources and research materials.\n\n8. **American Library (U.S. Consulate Library)**:\n   - Location: Bandra Kurla Complex (BKC)\n   - Highlights: A specialized library offering access to a wide range of American literature, research journals, and digital resources.\n\nThese libraries represent Mumbai's rich cultural and educational landscape, offering a variety of resources for scholars, students, and casual readers alike.",
